Capital FM photojournalist Francis Mbatha has been missing since August 6. Mbatha was last seen leaving him house shortly after returning from work. The 35-year-old's phone was last traced to Mombasa. Mbatha weights 65 kgs and has brown eyes and a bald head. On Twitter, he describes himself as a child of God, journalist, husband and proud father. Mbatha's relatives, Capital FM owner and businessman Chris Kirubi and the media fraternity have asked the public for help in finding him. "Help the Capital FM family find our photojournalist," Kirubi wrote on Twitter. Members of the public were asked to call 020 2210020, 0724 257 065 or go to the nearest police stations with their reports. Click here for the latest political news